import React from "react";

import NavigationButton from "./navigation-button"
import TitleBold from "./text-title";
import styles from "./navigation.module.css"
import {Twitter, Home, Explore, Notification, Messages, Bookmark, Lists, Profile, More} from "./icons"

const MENU = [
  {
    key: "home",
    icon: <Home />,
    title: "Home"
  }
]

function Navigation(flat = false, keyName){
  return (
  <nav className={styles.nav}>
    <NavigationButton>
      <Twitter />
    </NavigationButton>

    {MENU.map((menu) => (
       <NavigationButton selected={keyName.selectedKey === menu.key}>
       <Home />
       <TitleBold>{menu.title}</TitleBold>
     </NavigationButton>
    ))}
   

    <NavigationButton selected={keyName.selectedKey === 'explore'}>
      <Explore />
      <TitleBold>Explore</TitleBold>
    </NavigationButton>

    <NavigationButton notify={2} selected={keyName.selectedKey === 'notification'}>
      <Notification />
      <TitleBold>Notification</TitleBold>
    </NavigationButton>

    <NavigationButton selected={keyName.selectedKey === 'messages'}>
      <Messages />
      <TitleBold >Messages</TitleBold>
    </NavigationButton>

    <NavigationButton selected={keyName.selectedKey === 'bookmark'}>
      <Bookmark />
      <TitleBold>Bookmark</TitleBold>
    </NavigationButton>

    <NavigationButton selected={keyName.selectedKey === 'lists'}>
      <Lists />
      <TitleBold>Lists</TitleBold>
    </NavigationButton>

    <NavigationButton selected={keyName.selectedKey === 'profile'}>
      <Profile />
      <TitleBold>Profile</TitleBold>
    </NavigationButton>

    <NavigationButton selected={keyName.selectedKey === 'more'}>
      <More />
      <TitleBold>More</TitleBold>
    </NavigationButton>
  </nav>
  )
}

export default Navigation
